 As a farmer I am happy about the early inputs distribution and look forward to the Command Agriculture programme succeeding like it did last year. My plea is that businesses also support Government efforts. Now more than ever we need to work together as Zimbabweans. If we believe in each other and support each other’s efforts, we can be successful. — Anon Do police need a search warrant before they can conduct a search of any properties in Zimbabwe or just a tip off? — Reader  Readers are invited to send comments and feedback to our new number: 0774 457 529. All sms or WhatsApp contributions must include the sender’s name or pseudonym as well as town or home area. Since the Chronicle is published in English, we would prefer our readers to write in English. — Editor.